sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Dev as Developer (User)
    participant O as Orchestrator (build.py)
    participant FS as Local Filesystem (/build_output)
    participant D as Docker Daemon
    participant U as Upstream Source (e.g., gnu.org)
    
    Dev->>O: `./build.py blueprints/base/base.yaml`
    activate O
    
    O->>O: Parse YAML (Sources, SHA256, Build Steps)
    O->>FS: Dynamically generate temporary `Dockerfile`
    
    O->>D: Trigger `docker build` using generated `Dockerfile`
    activate D
    
    D->>D: Spin up ephemeral Debian compiler sandbox
    
    D->>U: `curl` target source `.tar.gz` and signatures
    activate U
    U-->>D: Return raw payload
    deactivate U
    
    D->>D: Compute SHA256 checksum locally
    
    alt Signature Fails
        D-->>O: Throw Exit 1 (Abort)
    else Signature Matches
        D->>D: Unpack `.tar.gz` payload natively
        D->>D: Execute `MAKE` & `CONFIGURE` strictly to `/sovereignforge_out`
    end
    
    O->>D: Request second build phase (Extract to scratch)
    D->>D: Pivot root base `FROM scratch`
    D->>D: `COPY --from=compiler /sovereignforge_out /`
    
    D-->>O: Commit final native OCI image to cache
    deactivate D
    
    O->>FS: Clean up temporary `Dockerfile` / staging directory
    O-->>Dev: Print "✅ Success! Image compiled natively"
    deactivate O
